      "message": "The method that I used to get the platform ids is not completely correct. I looked at the set of boards/platform that ran in the lab recently and removed the known boards that supported AX from that list. I then iteratively swapped out known instances where the mosys value of the board was actually something unexpected (i.e jacuzzi, scarlet, atlas, etc). I\u0027m not sure if there\u0027s a clean way to get the correct platform-name value right now.\n\nThe CQ served as a sanity check for the blocklist as wifi.HeCaps (previously known as network.WifiHeCaps) would fail in the dry run if it ran on a non-ax enabled deviced (which would indicate a hole in the list) which happened when I didn\u0027t include the proper value for atlas.",
